A nervous young man approaches Ava at the table.
Young Man: Ms… Ms—Ms. Sweet Spike! C-C-Can I get an a-autograph??? My hat! P-Please autograph my hat!
Ava: Eh? You think I would soil my name by putting it on some random loser’s hat?
Ava: Tch, tell you what, if I see you at the show, then maybe I’ll think about looking in your direction.
Ava: For now, get the fuck out of my sight.
Young Man: Th-THANK YOU SWEET SPIKE! I LOVE YOU!
The Young Man leaves the cafe. He looks quite excited.
Jade: Woah, that was pretty harsh. I thought you were… you know, sweet? You turned into a bad guy?
Ava: Yeah, I was sweeter before the injury, but AOW wants me to be heel for my return to D-1.
Ava: Makes sense you didn’t know I was heel because you couldn't watch D-3. But yeah, I’m a heel now.

Tokens.text: Jade: Heel? Like, the bad guy, right? Sorry, still getting used to the terminology.
Jade: So, the bad guy is called a heel around here? Sorry, still getting used to the terminology.
Jade: You’re supposed to boo the heel, right? The bad guy. Sorry, still getting used to the terminology.
Jade: Back from where I'm from, Cascadia, we never really used the terms.
Jade: We just kind of went with the fans on who they wanted to cheer or boo that night.
Jade: Is AOW that strict about that kind of thing? Always being your character and everything?
Ava: Well, not so much in D-1, but in the lower divisions? Absolutely. Especially in D-3.
Ava: People really want to believe that whatever they’re watching is real. Even if it’s painfully obvious that it’s not.
Ava: So, outside of the ring, you gotta make sure to act the same.
Ava: You know, kayfabe, presenting everything that happening in-ring like it’s real? Have to keep up the act in and outside of the ring.
Jade: I guess I never thought much of it. There wasn’t much room to believe what was happening was real where I was.
Jade: A bunch of the other wrestlers were less than half organic.
Ava: That does remind me, you have to tell me what made you want to stay full organic some time.
Jade: Maybe... It's a long story.
Ava: All good! We can trade stories whenever you want.
Ava: Anyway, you have a match coming up Monday right? We should definitely talk about it for a bit.
Ava: Silly, can’t be here, we need somewhere super secret! Like the AOW gym or something.
